com.camerontec.catalys.mis.eps.escalationpaths.runtime.actions

Class SampleSNMPAction

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.camerontec.catalys.mis.eps.escalationpaths.runtime.actions.AbstractAction
      • com.camerontec.catalys.mis.eps.escalationpaths.runtime.actions.BaseSNMPAction
        • com.camerontec.catalys.mis.eps.escalationpaths.runtime.actions.SampleSNMPAction
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    IAction, com.camerontec.catalys.mis.eps.IPersistable, Cloneable

    public class SampleSNMPAction
extends BaseSNMPAction
    Sample SNMP action implementation based on the assumption that the FIX-MONITORING MIB (see below) is used. In the case of SNMP v1 traps, we use a specific trap value of 1. In the case of SNMP v2c or above, we add a variable binding corresponding to the trap's OID as defined in the MIB. In both cases, we add two extra variable bindings to the PDU:
    • A representation of the session's name of the form <host>:<application name>:<session name>
    • A representation of the session's status as per the enum defined in the MIB (1 -> up, 2 -> down, 3 -> unknown)
    Below is the full definition of the FIX-MONITORING MIB that this sample action uses: 
     FIX-MONITORING-MIB DEFINITIONS ::= BEGIN

 IMPORTS
     OBJECT-TYPE, NOTIFICATION-TYPE, MODULE-IDENTITY, enterprises
         FROM SNMPv2-SMI

     TEXTUAL-CONVENTION, DisplayString
   FROM SNMPv2-TC;

 myCompany MODULE-IDENTITY
     LAST-UPDATED "201210050000Z"
     ORGANIZATION "My Company"
     CONTACT-INFO "TBD"
     DESCRIPTION "Initial draft"
     ::= { enterprises 2021 }

 fixMonitoring                OBJECT IDENTIFIER ::= { myCompany 1 }
 fixSessionStatusTraps        OBJECT IDENTIFIER ::= { fixMonitoring 1 }
 fixSessionStatusTrapsPrefix  OBJECT IDENTIFIER ::= { fixSessionStatusTraps 1 }
 fixSessionStatusTrapsObjects OBJECT IDENTIFIER ::= { fixSessionStatusTraps 2 }

 fixSessionName ::= TEXTUAL-CONVENTION
     STATUS       current
     DESCRIPTION "The name of a FIX session."
     SYNTAX       DisplayString (SIZE (0..255))

 fixSessionStatus ::= TEXTUAL-CONVENTION
     STATUS       current
     DESCRIPTION "The status of a FIX session."
     SYNTAX       INTEGER { up(1), down(2), unknown(3) }

 fixSessionStatusTrapSessionName OBJECT-TYPE
     SYNTAX      fixSessionName
     MAX-ACCESS  accessible-for-notify
     STATUS      current
     DESCRIPTION
       "The name of a FIX session, to be used in the payload of a FIX session status trap."
 ::= { fixSessionStatusTrapsObjects 1 }

 fixSessionStatusTrapSessionStatus OBJECT-TYPE
     SYNTAX      fixSessionStatus
     MAX-ACCESS  accessible-for-notify
     STATUS      current
     DESCRIPTION
       "The status of a FIX session, to be used in the payload of a FIX session status trap."
 ::= { fixSessionStatusTrapsObjects 2 }

 fixSessionStatusTrap NOTIFICATION-TYPE
 STATUS current
 OBJECTS { fixSessionStatusTrapSessionName, fixSessionStatusTrapSessionStatus }
 DESCRIPTION "Trap conveying a change in the status of a FIX session"
 ::= { fixSessionStatusTrapsPrefix 1 }

 END
